OL,3,CCouncil introduces school ice cream
OL,4,Cvan ban
OL,6,FBarnsley Council has introduced a ban
OL,7,Fon ice cream vans within 100 metres of
OL,8,Fschools in the area.JThe council's
OL,9,Fcabinet approved the ban at a meeting
OL,10,Fon Tuesday, 11 June, but all of the
OL,11,Flocal authority's councillors will
OL,12,Fhave the chance to vote on a range of
OL,13,Fmeasures affecting street traders.JNew
OL,14,Frules would mean mobile traders,
OL,15,Fincluding ice cream vans, will not be
OL,16,Fallowed to stop in one place for more
OL,17,Fthan 20 minutes and must not stop
OL,18,Fwithin 100 metres of the main entrance
OL,19,Fto schools 'without written consent'.
OL,20,FMobile traders will be banned from
OL,21,FBarnsley town centre and businesses
OL,22,Fwhose hygiene rating falls below three
OL,23,Fout of five stars will have their
OL,24,Fstreet trading consent suspended.
